<emphasis id="FB94EAD52A0BFFFFFB05FE44F8227B61" box="[1203,1406,506,532]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">Lebbeus fujimotoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the slender, slightly sinuous rostrum with six dorsal (the anteriormost tooth is located at the midlength) and nine ventral teeth and the possession of an epipod on the pereopod 1. In the 
<typeStatus id="165B88652A0BFFFFFC75FDFCFEAF7B29" box="[963,1011,578,604]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">type</typeStatus>
specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="0EE04D442A0BFFFFFB2EFDFDF8477B29" authorityName="Matsuzaki, Hibino &amp; Komai" authorityYear="2015" box="[1176,1307,578,604]" class="Malacostraca" family="Thoridae" genus="Lebbeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fujimotoi">
<emphasis id="FB94EAD52A0BFFFFFB2EFDFDF8477B29" box="[1176,1307,578,604]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">L. fujimotoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, consisting of 
<specimenCount id="DFE6FD4E2A0BFFFFFF03FDD8FC1E7BF5" box="[181,322,614,640]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" type="female">four females</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount id="DFE6FD4E2A0BFFFFFECEFDD8FCBD7BF5" box="[376,481,614,640]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
, the rostrum is noticeably curved dorsally, with four dorsal and seven or eight ventral teeth; the anteriormost tooth of the dorsal rostral series is located at the proximal 0.2–0.3; the pereopod 1 is devoid of epipod (
<bibRefCitation id="AD714B362A0BFFFFFEA4FD10FF537BBC" author="Matsuzaki, K. &amp; Hibino, M. &amp; Komai, T." box="[274,527,686,713]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" pagination="309 - 318" refId="ref16905" refString="Matsuzaki, K., Hibino, M. &amp; Komai, T. (2015) A new species of the caridean shrimp genus Lebbeus White, 1847 (Crustacea: Decapoda: Thoridae) from the southwestern Sea of Okhotsk, Hokkaido, Japan. Zootaxa, 4032 (3), 309 - 318. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4032.3.6" type="journal article" year="2015">
Matsuzaki 
<emphasis id="FB94EAD52A0BFFFFFE27FD11FC9F7BBD" box="[401,451,686,712]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
). Nevertheless, the COI sequence of the male specimen is almost identical (K2P divergence 0.3%; 
<tableCitation id="8462037C2A0BFFFFFED1FD6CFCE07B99" box="[359,444,722,748]" captionStart="TABLE 3" captionStartId="24.[149,237,541,567]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="TABLE 3. K2P divergences of the mitochondrial COI gene sequences among species of Lebbeus. Standard error estimates are shown above the diagonal. Codon positions included were 1st+2nd+3rd. All ambiguous positions were removed for each sequence pair (pairwise deletion option). There were a total of 604 bp in the final dataset." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/9D9F664F2A04FFF0FF23FDA3FA2E7B2E" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" tableUuid="9D9F664F2A04FFF0FF23FDA3FA2E7B2E">Table 3</tableCitation>
) with that of one of the ovigerous female specimen (CBM-ZC 16704), which closely agrees with the 
<typeStatus id="165B88652A0BFFFFFEFDFD48FC277A65" box="[331,379,758,784]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">type</typeStatus>
series in morphological aspects. Consequently, the male specimen is referred to 
<taxonomicName id="0EE04D442A0BFFFFFAA7FD49F8C97A65" authorityName="Matsuzaki, Hibino &amp; Komai" authorityYear="2015" box="[1297,1429,758,784]" class="Malacostraca" family="Thoridae" genus="Lebbeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fujimotoi">
<emphasis id="FB94EAD52A0BFFFFFAA7FD49F8C97A65" box="[1297,1429,758,784]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">L. fujimotoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This finding indicates that the development of epipod on the pereopod 1 is variable in 
<taxonomicName id="0EE04D442A0BFFFFFBE7FCA5F98F7A41" authorityName="Matsuzaki, Hibino &amp; Komai" authorityYear="2015" box="[1105,1235,794,820]" class="Malacostraca" family="Thoridae" genus="Lebbeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fujimotoi">
<emphasis id="FB94EAD52A0BFFFFFBE7FCA5F98F7A41" box="[1105,1235,794,820]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">L. fujimotoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Similar variation in the development of the epipod on the pereopod 1 is also known in 
<taxonomicName id="0EE04D442A0BFFFFFC7CFC81F91D7A2D" authorityName="Komai, Hayashi &amp; Kohtsuka" authorityYear="2004" box="[970,1089,830,856]" class="Malacostraca" family="Thoridae" genus="Lebbeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis id="FB94EAD52A0BFFFFFC7CFC81F91D7A2D" box="[970,1089,830,856]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">L. elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the another species normally lacking epipod on the pereopod 1 (Komai 
<emphasis id="FB94EAD52A0BFFFFFDC7FCDDFFFE7A09" box="[625,674,866,892]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">et al</emphasis>
. 2004).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C95F36C72A0BFFFFFF71FC38FCB77AB1" blockId="23.[151,1437,325,965]" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">
Genetic divergences between 
<taxonomicName id="0EE04D442A0BFFFFFDA1FC39FFC67AD5" authorityName="Matsuzaki, Hibino &amp; Komai" authorityYear="2015" box="[535,666,902,928]" class="Malacostraca" family="Thoridae" genus="Lebbeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fujimotoi">
<emphasis id="FB94EAD52A0BFFFFFDA1FC39FFC67AD5" box="[535,666,902,928]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="174">L. fujimotoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other known congeneric species are 3.3–24.9% (COI) (
<tableCitation id="8462037C2A0BFFFFFA88FC38F8CF7AD5" box="[1342,1427,902,928]" captionStart="TABLE 3" captionStartId="24.[149,237,541,567]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="TABLE 3. K2P divergences of the mitochondrial COI gene sequences among species of Lebbeus. Standard error estimates are shown above the diagonal. Codon positions included were 1st+2nd+3rd. All ambiguous positions were removed for each sequence pair (pairwise deletion option). There were a total of 604 bp in the final dataset." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/9D9F664F2A04FFF0FF23FDA3FA2E7B2E" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" tableUuid="9D9F664F2A04FFF0FF23FDA3FA2E7B2E">Table 3</tableCitation>
) and 1.1–6.8% (16S) (
<tableCitation id="8462037C2A0BFFFFFE30FC14FC817AB1" box="[390,477,938,964]" captionStart="TABLE 4" captionStartId="26.[149,237,747,773]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="TABLE 4. K2P divergences of the mitochondrial 16 rRNA gene sequences among species of Lebbeus. Standard error estimates are shown above the diagonal. All ambiguous positions were removed for each sequence pair (pairwise deletion option). There were a total of 570 bp in the final dataset." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/9D9F664F2A06FFF2FF23FD55F8E47A5C" pageId="23" pageNumber="174" tableUuid="9D9F664F2A06FFF2FF23FD55F8E47A5C">Table 4</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
